elementHandlerpkg

Class MatchHolder

  • java.lang.Object
    • elementHandlerpkg.MatchHolder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<MatchHolder>

    public class MatchHolder
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<MatchHolder>
    This class is a container class that holds the Element data from the SearchContainer and adds the additional wrapper of which patient's SearchContainer it came from. This is utilized by the MatchSelector's tree to keep track of which patient IDs are being used each row.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(MatchHolder a)
        This is a function for the tree in the MatchSelector and compares only on the patient IDs. Simply put this makes sure that the same patient isn't going to be in the list twice.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<MatchHolder>
        Parameters:
        a - A MatchHolder to compare it to.
        Returns:
        Returns -1 for greater than 1 for less than or 0 if both matched patients are the same matched patient.
